# Environment
.env
*.env

# Rust build outputs
/target/
**/*.rs.bk
Cargo.lock

# IDE
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*~

# Campsite logbook (SQLite database; ephemeral team coordination state)
# Anchored to repo root (`/campsites/`) so that `camp/src/campsites/`
# (the camp crate's campsite source modules) is NOT excluded.
/campsites/

# Camp v0.2 expeditions/ directory — substrate-resident team coordination
# (campsite metadata, signatures, activity log, field-track entries).
# Local-only by design; mirrors campsites/ exclusion above.
/expeditions/

# Scheduled-task lock dir (project-local Claude harness state; ephemeral)
.claude/

# AI-collaborator orientation file. Each developer may keep their own
# CLAUDE.md locally with paths/conventions tailored to their setup.
# README.md is the canonical project-orient for both humans and AI agents.
CLAUDE.md

# Design substrate. Lives locally for ongoing team development; not part of
# the published surface. Future externalization (sibling repo / GH Pages /
# etc.) is an open decision; for now substrate stays local.
docs/expedition/
sweeps/

# Adopter / internal-dev feedback notes. Local dev substrate (like
# docs/expedition/), not part of the published surface; the dogfood team
# reads them locally. Externalization is a future decision.
agent-feedback/

# Empty/transient working dirs
.captured-shape/

# Ad-hoc scan/audit JSON dumps + captured build/test/error logs at the repo
# root (e.g. `cargo antigen scan --format json > scan_out.json`, or
# `cargo build 2>build_f5.log`). Transient debugging artifacts, not part of the
# source surface. Globs cover numbered/suffixed variants.
/scan_out*.json
/audit_out*.json
/*.scan.json
/*.log

# Captured cargo build/test stdout/stderr redirected to root-level .txt files
# (e.g. `cargo test 2>test_output.txt`). Multi-agent teammates redirect cargo
# output to ad-hoc files at the repo root; they are transient and must not be
# committed. Note: real source/doc .txt (none currently at root) would need an
# explicit un-ignore. Also catches the malformed `R:antigen<...>.txt` artifact
# produced when a `2>R:\antigen<file>` redirect drops the path separator.
/*.txt
/R\:antigen*.txt

# Camp per-project crate — externalized from public surface 2026-05-22
# alongside docs/expedition/ and campsites/. Lives locally as canonical
# dogfood (antigen using antigen for its own team coordination), but not
# part of the published repo. Future-anyone reading antigen's source
# won't see camp/; the canonical adopter-facing camp lives at
# ~/.claude/skills/camp/ (camp-rs Rust source + dist binary) and in the
# camp documentation when published.
/camp/

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
